tive is diagnosed with lung cancer, yet the tumors seem to wax and wane inexplicably. Written for the lay person who wishes to better grasp how doctors decipher the myriad clues and puzzling symptoms they often encounter, each story presents a very different case where doctors must work to find the accurate diagnosis before it is too late. Edlow uses his unique ability to relate complex medical concepts in a writing style that is clear, engaging and easily understandable. The resulting stories both entertain us and teach us much about medicine, its history and the subtle interactions among pathogens, humans, and the environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aMedicinevCase studies. 0aMedicinexCase studies. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300154993423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300154993.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles